CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 12, 1966, pg. 1B reads: "Camera Bug - Just as "camera bug" Terrill Jackson was about to take a picture of lovely Ruth Greenlee, Courier photographer Charles "Teenie" Harris got this picture of the couple. Jackson is holding his camera in his hand."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Ruth Greenlee and Terrill Jackson, posed in Penn Sheraton Hotel for Kappa Alpha Psi Silhouettes Black and White Ball
